properties.description: A validator for NoteEdges in a Diagram, checking if they satisfy specific constraints related to their start and end nodes.

properties.docComment: A straight dotted line.
properties.description: A renderer for note edges in a diagram, with specified line and arrow head styles.

properties.docComment: An event handler with a name.
properties.description: A named event handler in JavaFX, allowing for delegation of event handling to another handler while maintaining a specific name for identification.

properties.docComment: A state node in a state diagram.

properties.description: A package node in a UML diagram, containing methods to add, remove, clone, and translate child nodes within the package.

properties.description: A validator for State Diagrams, containing constraints and methods to validate the structure of the diagram.

properties.docComment: Default implementation of the rendering operations.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering diagrams by providing methods for rendering diagram elements, calculating bounds, handling selection, and managing element renderers.

properties.docComment: A media type for a tip element.
properties.description: Different types of media (text and image) that can be used in a GUI for displaying tips.

properties.docComment:

properties.description: A grid system with a specific size and color for snapping points and rectangles to grid lines.

properties.docComment: Validator for object diagrams.
properties.description: A validator for object diagrams, containing constraints, valid edge and node types, and methods to check for valid diagram nodes and validate object diagrams.

properties.description: A diagram element with a method to retrieve its associated properties.

Represents an operation to change a diagram, that
can be undone. Operations are only required to be valid
for a single execution and a single undoing in a row.
properties.description: A contract for classes that define operations to be executed and undone on a diagram.

properties.docComment: An initial in a state diagram.
properties.description: A final state node in a UML diagram.

properties.docComment:
A layout that presents the properties of a DiagramElement
 and allow editing them.
properties.description: A GUI component that displays and allows editing of properties for a specific `DiagramElement`, with various editor controls and features such as tabbing and stereotype delimiter insertion.

properties.docComment:
Stores a set of diagram elements for the purpose of pasting into a diagram.

Copying a list of elements into the clipboard results in a number of transformations
to the list and its elements to render the elements suitable for pasting:
- All elements are cloned
- Dangling edges are removed
- Nodes requiring a missing parent are removed
- Dangling references to parents are removed
- The nodes are repositioned so that the top left coordinate of the set of elements
  is at the origin (0,0).
  
The list of elements stored into the clipboard is assumed to respect the non-redundancy 
constraint that no element whose deletion leads to the deletion of a node is selected with the node.

The clipboard is a singleton. This is necessary to allow copying elements
between diagrams of the same type.

Currently pasting into a sequence diagram is not permitted as the semantics are 
ambiguous.
properties.description: A singleton clipboard object that stores copied diagram elements (nodes and edges) and provides methods for managing and manipulating these elements.

properties.docComment: Represents a version of JetUML.
properties.description: A version number with major, minor, and patch components, providing methods for comparison, compatibility checking, creation, parsing, and string representation.

properties.docComment: Possible directionalities for an association.
properties.description: The directionality of a dependency edge in a UML diagram, with options for unidirectional and bidirectional relationships.

properties.docComment:
Parses arrays in JSON document according to the ECMA-404 2nd edition December
2017. Also provides support for writing strings in JSON standard.
properties.description: A parser for parsing and converting JSON arrays from a character buffer and Java objects.
Provides a set of classes and interfaces for building and manipulating various types of diagrams, such as class diagrams, object diagrams, sequence diagrams, state diagrams, and use case diagrams.

properties.docComment: A category for the error.
properties.description: Different categories of deserialization exceptions, including SEMANTIC, STRUCTURAL, and SYNTACTIC.

properties.docComment: An object to render a UseCaseNode.

properties.docComment: A utility class to draw various graphics for diagram handling tools.
properties.description: A utility class for rendering graphics in a JetUML application, providing methods for drawing shapes, handles, lassos, rubberbands, and applying styling to paths and lines on a JavaFX canvas.

properties.docComment: There can't be an edge of the given type between the same node.

properties.docComment: Represents an error while parsing JSON text.
properties.description: An exception that occurs during JSON parsing, storing the character position where the exception occurred.

properties.docComment:
A Singleton that manages all user preferences global to
the application.
properties.description: A singleton object that manages boolean and integer user preferences, allowing for retrieval, setting, and notification of preference changes through handlers.

properties.docComment:
Base class for nodes and edges. Responsible for storing the single
Properties object used to describe the properties of this element.
There is only a single Properties object associated with a DiagramElement, 
used to represent the element's properties through its life-cycle.
properties.description: A diagram element with properties that can be initialized, cloned, and accessed.

properties.docComment: A builder for use case diagram.
properties.description: A builder for creating Use Case diagrams by initializing with a Diagram object of type USECASE.

properties.docComment: An object to render a package in a class diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for package description nodes in a diagram, providing methods for creating icons, drawing contents, and calculating bounds.

properties.docComment: An object to render a NoteNode.
properties.description: A renderer for note nodes in a diagram, providing methods for creating and drawing note shapes, calculating dimensions, and initializing with a parent DiagramRenderer.

properties.docComment:
A fixed-sized queue for storing a list of 
files recently manipulated by the application.
properties.description: A queue of recent files with a maximum capacity of 5, providing methods to add files, deserialize and serialize file lists, retrieve the most recent directory, iterate over files, and get the current size of the queue.

properties.docComment: An object to render an implicit parameter in a Sequence diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering graphical representations of Implicit Parameter Nodes in diagrams, providing methods for creating icons, drawing nodes, calculating dimensions, and handling node connections.

properties.docComment: An edge with three labels.
properties.description: A diagram edge with three labels, allowing for customization of the start and end labels.

properties.docComment:
A modal dialog that allows the user to edit the 
properties of a DiagramElement.
properties.description: A dialog window for editing properties of a diagram element in a JavaFX application.

properties.docComment:
A note node in a UML diagram. The name of the node
 is the text of the note.
properties.description: A note node in a UML diagram.

properties.docComment:
Stores the logical structure of a diagram. This class is only concerned with 
maintaining information about the logical structure of a diagram (nodes and edges). 
Specifically, it should not encode any business rules about the valid construction
of diagrams (handled by DiagramBuilder), or of computing the geometry of a diagram
(handled by DiagramView). DiagramData provides immutable access to the information
stored in the diagram.
properties.description: A diagram object containing edges, root nodes, and methods for managing and manipulating the elements within the diagram.

properties.docComment: An object to render a package in a class diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for package nodes in a diagram, providing methods to calculate bounding rectangles and positions based on the dimensions and positions of child nodes.

properties.docComment:
Helper class for the DiagramCanvas that computes the difference in position
of diagram nodes being moved.
properties.description: A utility for tracking the movement of diagram nodes by storing their original bounds and calculating their final positions.

properties.docComment: A return can only be between call nodes.
properties.description: A validator for checking if an edge in a diagram is a return edge between two call nodes.

properties.docComment: A reference edge can only be between an object node and a field node.
properties.description: A validator for ensuring that an edge in a diagram is a valid object reference edge connecting a field node to an object node.

properties.docComment: Can draw a straight edge with a label than can be obtained dynamically.
properties.description: A renderer for drawing labeled straight edges on a diagram, including methods for rendering the edge itself, calculating bounding rectangles, extracting labels, and wrapping label text.

properties.docComment: Represents one side of a rectangular node.
properties.description: The four cardinal directions (TOP, RIGHT, BOTTOM, LEFT) and provides methods to determine if a side is horizontal or vertical, get the mirrored side, and initialize new instances.

properties.docComment: A type that allows to check the Diagram's semantic validity.
properties.description: A validator for diagrams that can check if a diagram is valid and provide information on any validation errors.

properties.docComment: Internal observer of key events.
properties.description: A handler for key events, providing methods to handle typed keys and notify when the shift key is pressed.

properties.docComment: Class that statically loads the tips.

properties.docComment: An object to render a PointNode.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering and interacting with point nodes in a diagram.

properties.docComment: The main frame that contains panes that contain diagrams.
properties.description: The main editor frame of the JetUML application, providing functionality for managing and displaying diagram tabs, recent files, menu items, and various actions related to editing, saving, exporting, and duplicating diagrams.

properties.docComment:
An event handler whose callback has the effect of opening a new 
diagram in the EditorFrame.
properties.description: A handler for creating new diagrams of a specific type, delegating event handling to another handler.

properties.description: A Java application for creating and editing UML diagrams, with fields for version information and host services, and methods for opening files, initializing the application, opening a web browser, setting stage boundaries, and starting the application.

properties.docComment:
Script to generate the user guide by collecting all the tips of the day in a single page.
The user guide is created by expanding a template md file with HTML content 
to show all the tips in collapsible elements.
properties.description: A utility for generating a user guide by dynamically replacing placeholders in a template file with tips in HTML format and writing the result to an output file.

properties.docComment: Validator for sequence diagrams.
properties.description: A validator for sequence diagrams, containing fields for valid node and edge types, as well as constraints, and methods for checking the validity of diagram nodes and ensuring there is at most one root node in the diagram.

properties.docComment: Represents a pair of width and height.
properties.description: A geometric dimension with width and height values, providing methods for comparison, hashing, manipulation, and string representation.

properties.docComment: Possible directionalities for an association.
properties.description: The directionality of an association edge in a UML diagram, with options for unidirectional, bidirectional, and unspecified directionality.

properties.docComment: An edge that joins two call nodes.
properties.description: A directed edge in a UML diagram that can either be a signal or not, with methods for determining if it is a self-edge and for setting and getting the signal attribute.

properties.docComment: Validator for use case diagrams.
properties.description: A validator for Use Case diagrams, containing valid node and edge types as well as constraints for validating Use Case diagrams.

properties.docComment:
A collection of utility methods to deal with general
GUI concerns.
properties.description: A utility class with static fields and methods for calculating default dimensions and bounds for GUI elements in a JavaFX application.

properties.docComment: Singleton object that manages the notification object positions and display states.
properties.description: A service that manages the display and positioning of notifications on the main stage of a JavaFX application.

properties.docComment: An edge in a diagram.
properties.description: A connection between two nodes in a diagram, providing methods to clone the edge, connect nodes, and retrieve the starting and ending nodes.

properties.docComment: A builder for class diagrams.
properties.description: A builder for creating and manipulating class diagrams, providing methods for adding, linking, and unlinking nodes within the diagram.

properties.docComment:
Parses strings in JSON document according to the ECMA-404 2nd
edition December 2017. Also provides support for writing strings 
in JSON standard.
properties.description: A utility for parsing and handling JSON strings, including escaping special characters and converting Java objects to JSON-formatted strings.

properties.docComment: An edge that that represents a generalization of a use case.
properties.description: A generalization edge in a UML use case diagram.

properties.docComment: Documents a class as generating immutable objects.

properties.description: Provides classes and utilities for managing and displaying tips or user guides in a graphical user interface (GUI) application.

properties.docComment: A package description node in a UML diagram.
properties.description: A node in a UML diagram that contains a package description with methods to build properties, clone, get and set contents.

properties.docComment:
Services for saving and loading Diagram objects. The files are encoded
in UTF-8.

properties.docComment:
A modal dialog that allows users to change the duration (in seconds) that
notifications remain visible.

properties.docComment: An object that can respond to the mouse being dragged.

properties.description: A renderer for stored edges in a UML diagram, providing methods for rendering the edge path, arrow heads, labels, and selection handles.

properties.docComment: A tip that contains TipElement instances.
properties.description: A tip with a title, ID, list of elements, and methods for converting JSON objects to tip elements and determining media types used in the tip.

properties.docComment: Represents an error while processing JSON data.
properties.description: An exception related to JSON processing with constructors for specifying error messages and causes.

properties.docComment:
A tab that allow users to open new diagrams of the different types
or open recently saved diagrams.
properties.description: A GUI component in the JetUML application that displays a welcome tab with panels for creating new diagrams, displaying files, showing copyright information, and loading recent file links.

properties.docComment: A transition can only end in a final node or a state node or a note node.
properties.description: A validator for ensuring that a StateTransitionEdge in a diagram ends at either a FinalStateNode or a StateNode.

properties.docComment: Type of UML generalization relation.
properties.description: Different types of generalization edges in a UML diagram, including Implementation and Inheritance.

properties.docComment:
Represents a property of an object as a tuple that 
consists of a name, a getter for a value, and a setter
for that value. The values managed by a property should only be of immutable types.
properties.description: A property with a name, getter and setter functions, allowing for getting and setting values through these functions.

properties.docComment:
An operation that is composed of other operations, following
the Composite Design Pattern.

Executing a compound operation executes all the sub-operations
in the order they were added. Undoing a compound operation
undoes all the sub-operation in the reverse order in which 
they were added.

properties.docComment: The renderer for object diagrams.
properties.description: A renderer for object diagrams that initializes element renderers for different types of nodes and edges in a given Diagram.

properties.docComment:
Wrapper around a DiagramRenderer that provides the logic for converting
requests to creates or remove nodes and edges, and convert these
requests into operation. An object of this class should perform
read-only access to the underlying diagram. However, executing the operations
created by methods of this class will change the state of the 
underlying diagram.
properties.description: A builder for creating and manipulating diagrams by providing methods for adding, removing, positioning, and connecting diagram elements while managing undo/redo functionality.

properties.docComment: There can be at most one caller to a call node.
properties.description: A constraint validator that ensures each CallNode in a diagram has at most one incoming CallEdge.

properties.docComment:
An object to render a class or interface in a class diagram.

The top box, which shows the title, has a minimum height of 20 pixels,
minus 20 if attributes are present, minus another 20 if methods are present.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering TypeNode elements in a diagram, providing methods for calculating dimensions, drawing the node on a canvas, and retrieving text information.

properties.docComment:
Represents an element (typically the diagram) that
can provide information about a diagram.
properties.description: A diagram data structure that contains methods for retrieving a list of edges and root nodes.

properties.docComment: Conversion utilities.
properties.description: A utility class for converting between JavaFX geometry objects and custom geometry objects from the org.jetuml.geom package.

properties.docComment: A tab holding a single diagram.
properties.description: A tab within a GUI that displays a diagram and provides methods for interacting with and manipulating the diagram.

properties.docComment:
Represents a simple (non-compound) operation. The operation
does no validation of the input method, so any code that 
constructs a SimpleOperation is responsible to ensure that,
when executed or undone, the operation will be valid.
properties.description: A simple operation with an associated reverse operation that can be executed and undone.
Provides classes and utilities for persisting and serializing JetUML diagrams.

properties.docComment: Represents a problem that invalidates a diagram for rendering in JetUML.
properties.description: A violation in a UML diagram, with fields for descriptor and category, and methods for creating new violations, determining category type, and retrieving violation description.

properties.docComment:
Represents the priority level for edges so that Layouter can lay out edges in a hierarchical order. 
Arranged in decreasing order of priority (INHERITANCE has the highest priority)
properties.description: Different priorities for edges in a UML diagram, including inheritance, self edges, aggregation, dependency, composition, association, other, and implementation, with methods to determine segmentation, stored status, and priority of edges.

properties.docComment: Validates that only note edges can point to point nodes.
properties.description: A constraint that validates whether an edge in a diagram connects to a point node, except in the case of a NoteEdge.

properties.docComment:
Attempts to parse an input text assumed to be in JSON notation
into a JsonObject. This implementation supports only a subset of the ECMA-404 2nd
edition (December 2017) standard. The standard is supported except for:
* Non-integer number values
* Null values
properties.description: A JSON parser that can parse JSON strings into JsonObject using a JsonObjectParser.

properties.docComment:
A class for handling the eight characters that can be escaped wit
another character in a JSON string: \", \\, \/, \b, \f, \n, \r, \t Note that
this does not include 'u', used for any unicode character.

In the documentation for this class, "symbol" refers to the character
following the escape (e.g., 'b' in "\b"), and "code point" refers to the code
point for that escape, in this case \b (backspace, U+0008)

This instance is stateless so it can be shared, but this is not enforced
(e.g., via a Singleton) in case it is more convenient to have multiple copies.
properties.description: A utility for handling special characters and their escape sequences in JSON format.

properties.docComment: An object node in an object diagram.
properties.description: A node in a UML diagram that can contain child nodes representing fields, with methods for adding, removing, and manipulating these child nodes.

properties.docComment: Implementation of the general scaffolding for validating a diagram.
properties.description: A validator for diagrams, providing methods to validate the structure and semantics of nodes and edges within the diagram.

properties.docComment: Prototype objects for creating diagram elements.
properties.description: A collection of predefined diagram element prototypes with associated keys and tooltip text retrieval functionality.

properties.docComment: An edge that joins the nodes in a constructor call.
properties.description: A constructor edge in a UML diagram with a middle label set to "create".

properties.docComment: An edge with a single middle label.
properties.description: A diagram edge with a single label that can be customized and accessed through various methods.

properties.docComment:
Responsible for executing and undoing operations, and managing the collection 
of previously executed and undone operations. Can also compute whether a 
diagram has unsaved modifications.
properties.description: A processor for managing diagram operations, including executing, undoing, redoing, and saving operations.

properties.docComment:
An edge that that represents a UML association, with optional 
 labels and directionality.
properties.description: An association edge in a UML diagram with a directionality property and methods to get and set the directionality value.

properties.docComment: An edge that joins two call nodes.
properties.description: A return edge in a UML diagram.

properties.docComment:
The different types of UML diagrams supported by 
this application.
properties.description: Different types of diagrams in a UML modeling tool, each with its own name, file extension, builder, renderer, validator, and list of prototype elements.

properties.docComment: A node with a name.
properties.description: A node in a diagram with a name property that can be accessed and modified.

properties.docComment: An actor node in a use case diagram.
properties.description: A node for an actor in a UML diagram with a default name of "Actor".

properties.docComment:
Parses any value in a JSON document according to the ECMA-404 2nd
edition December 2017.
properties.description: A parser for parsing any JSON value by iterating through a list of JSON value parsers and using the first applicable parser to parse the input.

properties.docComment:
The renderer for sequence diagrams. The implementation of this renderer assumes
that any sequence diagram has either zero call nodes or a single root call node, namely, 
only one call node with no callers.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering sequence diagrams, with fields for constants and mappings, and methods for computing node positions, drawing the diagram, finding nodes, and retrieving information about nodes and edges in the diagram.

properties.docComment:
Documents a class as a singleton that realizes the  
Singleton design pattern.

Converts a JSONObject to a diagram. Instances of this class are intended to be
used as a single-use wrapper around a JSON object that is to be decoded, as such
new JsonDecoder(pInputObject).decode()

The version information stored in a diagram file is purposefully discarded 
as JetUML no longer migrates versions. Storing and handling version numbers
is deemed not to be worth the complexity. In very rare cases were an decoding
issue might be due to versioning, users can always look at the text of the 
diagram file to recover the version number.
properties.description: A decoder for JSON representations of diagrams, with methods to extract and decode nodes, edges, and other properties from the input JSON object.

properties.docComment: An object to render a StateNode.
properties.description: A renderer for state nodes in a diagram, providing methods for drawing, determining connection points, and calculating bounds.

properties.docComment: Tip element represented as a Media/content pair.
properties.description: A tip element with content and media associated with it.

properties.docComment:
Base class for serialization and deserialization contexts. A context 
is a mapping between nodes and arbitrary identifiers. The only constraint
on identifiers is that they consistently preserve mapping between objects and
their identity.
properties.description: A context containing a diagram and a mapping of nodes to IDs, with methods for accessing and iterating over the nodes.

properties.docComment:
Represents the path of an edge on a diagram as a list of points. 
Non-segmented paths consist of 2 points (the start and end points).
properties.description: A path consisting of points that make up an edge, providing methods for accessing and manipulating these points.

properties.docComment: An object to render a call node in a Sequence diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for CallNode diagram elements in a JavaFX canvas, providing methods for drawing, calculating dimensions, and determining connection points.

properties.docComment:
Viewer for a labeled, straight edge with customized code to
compute connection points.
properties.description: A renderer for return edges in a diagram, providing methods to create an icon, calculate connection points, and render the return edge with specific styles and labels.

properties.docComment: A return edge must return to its caller, which must be a different node.
properties.description: A constraint validator that checks if a return edge in a diagram is correctly connected to a call edge.

properties.docComment: An object that can react to a change to a boolean user preference.
properties.description: A handler for notifying classes of changes to boolean preferences in user preferences.

properties.docComment: Validator for class diagrams.
properties.description: The class `org.jetuml.diagram.validator.ClassDiagramValidator` is a validator for class diagrams, containing constraints and methods to validate the structure of the diagram.

properties.docComment:
Utility methods to uniformly validate and access
Object instances as Json values.
properties.description: A utility class for validating and converting different types of JSON values.

properties.docComment: A line that connects a note to its attachment.
properties.description: A note edge in a UML diagram.

properties.docComment: An edge view specialized for state transitions.
properties.description: A renderer for state transition edges in a UML diagram, providing methods for drawing, labeling, and determining the shape of the edges.

properties.docComment: A straight solid line with an optional label.
properties.description: A renderer for object collaboration edges in a diagram, setting line style, arrow head, and middle label for the edge.

properties.docComment:
A selectable button that wraps a creation tool represented by an 
object prototype.
properties.description: A selectable tool button with an icon, tooltip, toggle group, and optional prototype `DiagramElement`.

properties.docComment:
Alert dialog specialized for displaying the various errors 
that can happen when opening a file.
properties.description: A Java class that handles displaying error alerts for deserialization errors, including specific details and additional information based on the type of exception thrown.
Provides a collection of classes and utilities for handling geometric calculations and operations in a two-dimensional space.

properties.docComment:
This class describes an immutable direction in the 2D plane. The
direction is conceptually represented as an angle in degrees between
0 and 359 inclusively, where 0 represents "up" or "north", and where
an increase in the angle moves the direction clockwise. A direction
can be expressed with a precision of a maximum of one degree.
properties.description: Directions in degrees and provides methods for calculating, manipulating, and comparing direction angles.

properties.docComment: An object to render an actor in a use case diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering actor nodes in a UML diagram, including methods for creating stick figure representations, drawing actor nodes on a canvas, and calculating bounding rectangles.

properties.docComment: Various text decorations.
properties.description: Different text decorations such as underlined, bold, and padded for rendering strings in Java.

properties.docComment:
Parses objects in JSON document according to the ECMA-404 2nd
edition December 2017. Also provides support for writing JsonObjects 
in JSON text.
properties.description: A parser for parsing and converting JSON objects from and to Java objects.

Converts a graph to JSON notation. The notation includes:
* The JetUML version
* The graph type
* An array of node encodings
* An array of edge encodings

A tracker for changes made to properties of a DiagramElement, allowing for tracking and reverting changes made in a dialog.

properties.docComment:
A sequence of characters with a current position, to facilitate processing
character input. Client code is expected to only invoke valid operations,
i.e., check whether there are sufficient characters left to read before
reading them.

The position of a character buffer corresponds to the position of the last
character read. This position is initialized at -1. A character buffer is
only expected to be traversed once.
properties.description: A character buffer that allows for navigation and manipulation of a string of characters.

properties.docComment: Static functions to compute the geometry of arrow heads and render them.
properties.description: A renderer for drawing arrow heads on lines in a UML diagram, providing methods for drawing, calculating bounds, and generating paths for arrow heads.

A modal dialog that allows users to change font
size of diagrams.
properties.description: A JavaFX dialog window for setting and validating font sizes within a specified range, with fields for minimum and maximum sizes, methods for creating buttons and form layout, retrieving and validating font sizes, handling user input, and displaying alerts for invalid sizes.

properties.docComment:
A utility class to determine various font position metrics
for the particular font.

A visual diagram for why the bounds values are what they are
(with word "Thy"):   ____________________
getMinY() (ascent)  |*****  *           |
                    |  *    *           |
                    |  *    *****   *  *|
                    |  *    *   *   *  *|
                    |  *    *   *   ****|
(baseline)          |------------------*| x=getWidth()
                    |                  *|
                    |                  *| 
y = 0  (descent)    |                ***|
                    |                   |
                    |                   |
getMaxY() (leading) |-------------------|

Hence, upon calling getHeight(), to get tight bounds, one should subtract
off the leading value (found by getting the max Y value of a one-lined text
box)
properties.description: A utility for calculating the dimensions of text rendered with a specific font in JavaFX.

properties.docComment:
Abstract strategy that describes objects that can draw and
compute various geometric properties of nodes.
properties.description: A renderer for nodes in a diagram, providing methods for managing storage, determining connection points, retrieving default dimensions, and retrieving faces of nodes.

properties.docComment:
A JSONObject is an unordered collection of name/value pairs referred to as
"properties". Its external form is a string wrapped in curly braces with
colons between the names and values, and commas between the values and names.
The values can be any of these types: Boolean, JsonArray, JsonObject,
Integer, String. Null values and non-integer number formats are not supported
by this implementation.

Any attempt at an illegal operation will raise a JsonException.

As an additional robustness feature, this class makes not type conversion.
This means that values can only be obtained in the same type as they were put
in. For example, putting a property "size" as a string will store it
internally as a string, and attempting to retrieve it as an int will throw a
JsonException.
properties.description: A JSON object with methods for retrieving, adding, and validating properties, as well as converting the object to a JSON string.

properties.docComment: A boolean preference.
properties.description: A set of boolean preferences with default values and methods to access and initialize them.

properties.docComment: A window that presents the tip of the day (by calling show()).
properties.description: A JavaFX dialog window that displays tips to the user, with customizable menu options and styling.

properties.docComment: An object to render an interface in a class diagram.
properties.description: A renderer for interface nodes in a UML diagram, providing methods for generating the text representation of an interface node's name and initializing the renderer with a specified parent.

properties.docComment:
A straight dotted line with a V end decoration and special icons 
to distinguish between dependency types.
properties.description: A renderer for Use Case Dependency edges in a diagram, providing methods to create an icon representation, retrieve an icon tag, and render the edge with specific style and properties.

properties.docComment:
A class for creating menus from strings in a resource bundle. The class does not 
depend on the Singleton ApplicationResource instance to improve testability.

An instance of this class is intended to be initialized with a resource bundle,
used to create any number of menus, then discarded.

The user data for a menu item is a boolean flag that indicates whether the
menu is only relevant to a current diagram (true) or generally relevant (false).

To create a menu item, the creation methods will look for the following resources
in the specified ApplicationResources object, with a key followed by a prefix P.

- P.text (required):        The text of the menu
- P.mnemonic (optional):    The single letter mnemonic for opening the menu with the keyboard 
- P.icon (optional):	 	   The path to the menu icon
- P.accelerator (optional): The shortcut key combination.  Add ".mac" for macs.
properties.description: A factory for creating JavaFX menu items and menus with specified prefixes, icons, mnemonics, accelerators, and event handlers, utilizing application resources and determining operating system compatibility.
Different categories of violations in a diagram validator, including SEMANTIC and STRUCTURAL.

properties.docComment: Provides shared services for viewing an edge.
properties.description: A renderer for edges in a diagram, providing methods for rendering, selecting, and calculating properties of edges.

properties.docComment:
An object responsible for computing the geometry of a diagram. This class is 
intended to be specialized by subclasses that correspond to different diagram
types. 

A rendering pass starts with a call to draw(...). This results in the complete
geometry of the diagram being computed, and some of the computations being cached.
Subsequent calls to query method will use the cached computations. 

A single instance of each specialized renderer is needed as long as the geometry
is recomputed with a call to draw before any querying of the diagram geometry.
properties.description: A renderer for rendering and interacting with diagram elements in a JavaFX canvas.

properties.docComment:
An invisible node that is used in the toolbar to draw an
 edge, and in notes to serve as an end point of the node
 connector.

properties.docComment:
An edge that that represents a UML aggregation or 
 composition, with optional labels.
properties.description: An aggregation edge in a UML diagram, with methods for setting and retrieving the type of the edge.

properties.docComment:
An edge that that represents a UML dependency
 between use cases.
properties.description: A Use Case Dependency Edge in a UML diagram, with a type field and methods for building properties, getting the type, and initializing instances with a specified type.

properties.docComment:
A node in a diagram.

Different node subclasses can potentially implement the 
child node and parent mixin behavior, depending on the needs
of the diagram type in which nodes participants.

Nodes that can act as child nodes can potentially be linked to a parent node. 

Nodes that can act as parent nodes can potentially have children nodes according 
to a diagram type-specific parent-child relation. Parent nodes control their
child nodes. If a child node has a parent, only the parent node is tracked by
the diagram object. If a parent node is removed from the diagram, all its children
are also removed. Cloning a parent node clones all the children, and similarly
with all other operations, including copying, translating, etc.
properties.description: A node in a diagram structure with methods for adding, removing, and manipulating child nodes, as well as retrieving information about the node's parent and position on the diagram.

properties.docComment: Represents the 4 corners of a node. Used to plan the placement of self-edges.
properties.description: Different corner positions of a node in a rendering, providing methods to determine horizontal and vertical indices, as well as horizontal and vertical sides associated with each corner.

properties.docComment: A builder for object diagram.
properties.description: A builder for constructing object diagrams, providing methods for adding nodes, edges, and performing operations related to object diagram elements.

properties.docComment:
An implicit parameter node in a sequence diagram. The 
visual portion of this node includes the top rectangle (object) and
its vertical life line. The ImplicitParamterNode's creator is the
CallNode that is the source of a "creates" edge that leads to 
this node, or null if this node is node created as part of the 
sequence.
properties.description: A node in a UML diagram that can have multiple `CallNode` children, with methods for adding, removing, and cloning child nodes.

properties.docComment:
A deserialization context allows clients to incrementally build
up the context. The identifiers that correspond to objects must be 
specified explicitly.
properties.description: A context for deserializing objects, specifically Nodes, within a Diagram.

properties.docComment: A class to collect and manage the properties of a diagram element. It is not possible to change a property once it's added to a Properties object. Properties objects are intended to be constructed once, then queried only. This class provides support for storing properties in a meaningful order. By default, this is the order of insertion. However, use of the method addAt allows client code to insert a property at a specific index. Keeping properties in order allows for uses such as displaying properties in a predictable order, for instance in GUI forms.
properties.description: A collection of properties with getter and setter functions, allowing for the addition, retrieval, and iteration over these properties.

properties.docComment:
Common data and implementation for the different flavors of 
package nodes. Package nodes have at least a name and a parent.
properties.description: A package node in a UML diagram with methods to link, unlink, and check for a parent container.

properties.docComment:
Represents indexed positions on the faces of nodes where edges can attach.
North-facing and South-facing sides of nodes have indices in range -4 to +4.
East and West-facing sides of nodes have indices in range -2 to +2.
properties.description: The enum `org.jetuml.rendering.edges.NodeIndex` represents different index values for connection points on a node face, along with methods to calculate the space between connection points and the position of a connection point on a line.

properties.docComment:
An edge that that represents a dynamic collaboration between
 two objects in an object diagram, with optional label.

properties.docComment:
There can't be both an association and an aggregation edge between two
nodes.
